**Missing `ContainerPort.Protocol` default — spurious Deployment/CronJob updates**

`ContainerDefaults` fills in `ImagePullPolicy`, `TerminationMessagePath`, and `TerminationMessagePolicy`, but omits port-level defaulting. The Kubernetes API server calls `SetDefaults_ContainerPort` on every stored container port and sets `Protocol: TCP` when the field is empty. If a caller declares container ports without an explicit `Protocol` (a common pattern), `existingSpec.Containers[i].Ports[j].Protocol == "TCP"` while `desiredSpec.Containers[i].Ports[j].Protocol == ""`. Because `apiequality.Semantic` falls back to `reflect.DeepEqual` for string fields, `"" != "TCP"` — so `EnsureDeployment` detects a spec change and calls `c.Update` on every reconcile.

All existing tests use containers that either declare no ports at all or explicitly set `Protocol: corev1.ProtocolTCP`, so this gap is not caught.

Add a protocol default loop inside `ContainerDefaults`:

```suggestion
// ContainerDefaults fills in the API-server defaults for each container:
// ImagePullPolicy, TerminationMessagePath, TerminationMessagePolicy, and
// ContainerPort.Protocol.
func ContainerDefaults(containers []corev1.Container) {
	for i := range containers {
		if containers[i].ImagePullPolicy == "" {
			containers[i].ImagePullPolicy = DefaultImagePullPolicy(containers[i].Image)
		}
		if containers[i].TerminationMessagePath == "" {
			containers[i].TerminationMessagePath = corev1.TerminationMessagePathDefault
		}
		if containers[i].TerminationMessagePolicy == "" {
			containers[i].TerminationMessagePolicy = corev1.TerminationMessageReadFile
		}
		for j := range containers[i].Ports {
			if containers[i].Ports[j].Protocol == "" {
				containers[i].Ports[j].Protocol = corev1.ProtocolTCP
			}
		}
	}
}
```

